column5: Wow.................. It was crazy cold out this morning extremely windy.............Marked a few fish on the Marcum managed to catch one nice walleye............Caught on a large Buckshot and minnow...............Ice was 3-5" where we checked right in front of Fishmasters shop if anyone decides to go out make sure you talk to Steve there was open water in certain area's on the Grand yesterday.................Here's a couple picture's...............JHM
Beautiful 'eye i love that light colour they have sometimes.  Congrats.  -Ramble

I have seen a lot of walleye coming out of the River lately and it never ceases to amaze me how different each and every one looks.  The SEASONED fisherman knows all the reasons for this,  however being "new to catching fish" (Not new to fishing... ) I am forever intrigued.  Well Done Jeff... you certainly know how to find those fish!  Cheers,  Jen
nice eye you got that will make a nice snack  rob
Nice fish JHM ....how did that new hut work for ya ...see ya in the morning ..
Wow, nice one. Glad to see the river is still producing!
I love how you moved the fish a little closer to the 24" mark in that close-up shot....very clever...just kidding!!!   Nice fish man!
